                <ol class="rotation-steps">
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Activate Both Auras</strong> -- Keep Fanaticism Aura (Crit + Attack Speed) and Defiance Aura (Armor + Resistances + Unstoppable) active permanently. These are your core offensive and defensive buffers. Without both active, the build feels sluggish and squishy.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Build Fanaticism Stacks with Punish</strong> -- Use Punish to quickly ramp Fanaticism Aura stacks before engaging packs. Each stack increases Crit Chance and Attack Speed. Reach max stacks before diving into combat for optimal damage.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Cast Consecration under your feet</strong> -- Drop Consecration zones under yourself or in pack centers. The DoT damage layers on top of Blessed Hammer spirals, and the healing provides sustain during extended fights. Keep this active throughout combat.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Spam Blessed Hammer while moving</strong> -- This is your primary damage skill. Cast Blessed Hammer repeatedly while circling or moving through packs. The hammers spiral outward, hitting all enemies in their path. More casts = more hammers = more damage.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Position for maximum hammer coverage</strong> -- Blessed Hammer spirals outward in a predictable pattern. Position yourself so the hammers pass through enemy clusters. Good positioning doubles your effective damage by ensuring every hammer hits multiple targets.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Use Falling Star for repositioning</strong> -- Dash into packs or escape dangerous situations with Falling Star. The invulnerability frames provide emergency survivability, and the gap-close lets you position optimally for hammer spirals.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Maintain Fanaticism stacks during downtime</strong> -- If you stop attacking, Fanaticism stacks decay. Use Punish or Blessed Hammer during movement to maintain stacks. Losing stacks means losing Crit and Attack Speed, which kills your DPS.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Critical mass -- spam and spiral</strong> -- At high Fanaticism stacks and sufficient CDR, you can spam Blessed Hammer nearly off cooldown. Just keep moving and casting. The hammers handle the rest, spiraling through packs and clearing screens passively.</p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>

