                <h2>Gameplay Tips</h2>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Both auras must be active at all times.</strong>
                    <p>Fanaticism provides your Crit and Attack Speed scaling. Defiance provides your survivability. Fighting without either active is suicide. Check your buff bar regularly and recast if either drops off.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Hammer pathing matters more than you think.</strong>
                    <p>Blessed Hammer spirals outward in a fixed pattern. If you cast from the wrong position, hammers miss enemies entirely. Learn the spiral trajectory and position yourself so hammers pass through enemy clusters, not around them.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Keep moving while casting.</strong>
                    <p>Standing still makes you a sitting duck. Blessed Hammer can be cast while moving, so circle around packs or kite backward while spamming. This keeps you safe while maintaining full DPS output.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Consecration zones amplify your AoE.</strong>
                    <p>Don't skip Consecration. The DoT damage and healing it provides are substantial. Drop zones under pack centers or under yourself during stationary fights. The zone lasts several seconds, so you get massive value per cast.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Single-target is your weakness.</strong>
                    <p>Blessed Hammer excels against packs but struggles against solo bosses. Against bosses with no adds, your damage feels mediocre. Accept this limitation -- the build is designed for AoE farming, not boss deletion.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>CDR thresholds enable spam rotations.</strong>
